  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0db3 \u0dbb\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dba\u0dc5\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dda \u0d8b\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0dba\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "NASA is trying to relaunch the moon rocket",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ground crews at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida, USA, are nearing the second attempt to send NASA's next-generation giant moon rocket on its maiden test flight.",
        "The final full day of preparations for the launch has begun, five days after technical problems thwarted an initial attempt.",
        "Mission managers prepare to lift off the Space Launch System (SLS) rocket and its Orion space capsule Saturday afternoon to kick off NASA's Moon-to-Mars Artemis program, the successor to the Apollo lunar missions.",
        "Investigations on Thursday night revealed that technicians had fixed a leaking fuel line. That contributed to NASA's decision to halt Monday's initial launch mission, the space station's deputy program manager, Jeremy Parsons, told reporters.",
        "Two other major problems with the rocket, a faulty engine temperature sensor and some cracks in the insulating foam, have been largely resolved, Artemis mission manager Mike Sarafin told reporters.",
        "Accordingly, Melody Lovin, a launch weather officer for the US Space Force at Cape Canaveral, said the launch is expected to take place on Saturday at 2:17 p.m."
      ],
